 the Late Latin name <i>Aegidius</i>, from Greek <i>Aigidios</i> (a derivative of <i>aigidion</i> ‘kid, young goat’), via Old French <i>Gide</i>. It was the name of an 8th‐century saint who, according to tradition, was an Athenian citizen who fled to Provence because he could not cope with the fame and adulation caused by his power to work miracles, in particular by healing the lame and crippled. This was not a particularly common name in the Middle Ages and its use seems to have been confined to certain families and localities."],"variants":[{"name":"Gyles","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Giles ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Giles de Arderne was born before 1330, in Drayton, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Robert d'Arderne, was 89 and his mother, Nicola Bardolf, was 36. He married Margaret Molineux. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1376."},"et":{"Bef 1330–Abt 1376":"enne 1330–umbes 1376","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1318–1379":"1318–1379","1330–1376":"1330–1376","1324–1382":"1324–1382","1355–1375":"1355–1375","1240–1331":"1240–1331","1294–1365":"1294–1365","1330":"1330","1240":"1240","1294":"1294","1382":"1382","1315":"1315","1324":"1324","1379":"1379","1355":"1355","Abt 1376":"umbes 1376","1365":"1365","1376":"1376","Bef 1330":"enne 1330","1375":"1375","1331":"1331","about 1331":"umbes 1331","1318":"1318","Wappenham, Northamptonshire, England":"Wappenham, Northamptonshire, England","Drayton, Warwickshire, England":"Drayton, Warwickshire, England","Drayton, Oxfordshire, England":"Drayton, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Bef 1330–Abt 1376":"ennen vuotta 1330–noin 1376","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1318–1379":"1318–1379","1330–1376":"1330–1376","1324–1382":"1324–1382","1355–1375":"1355–1375","1240–1331":"1240–1331","1294–1365":"1294–1365","1330":"1330","1240":"1240","1294":"1294","1382":"1382","1315":"1315","1324":"1324","1379":"1379","1355":"1355","Abt 1376":"noin 1376","1365":"1365","1376":"1376","Bef 13